entry.tran: 不练达的；不谙世故的；不老练的
entry.def: If you describe someone as unworldly, you mean that they have not experienced many things in their life and do not know what sort of things usually happen to other people during their lives.

example.ex: She was so young, so unworldly...
example.tran: 她太年轻，太不懂人情世故。

example.ex: He is a little unworldly about such matters.
example.tran: 他在这些事情上不太老练。

entry.def: If you describe someone as unworldly, you mean that they are not interested in having a lot of money or possessions.

example.ex: Kitty's family was unworldly, unimpressed by power, or money.
example.tran: 基蒂一家清心寡欲，淡泊金钱与权力。

means.word_mean: 1. not concerned with the temporal world or swayed by mundane considerations;

sentences.sentence: "was unworldly and did not greatly miss worldly rewards"- Sheldon Cheney

means.word_mean: 2. not wise in the ways of the world;

sentences.sentence: "either too unsophisticated or too honest to promise more than he could deliver"
